trend_summary: Across the image sequence, the mature suburb remains largely intact; growth occurs mainly through small-parcel infill and a few new subdivisions at the fringe. Commercial blocks densify, roads stay fixed, and tree canopy gradually thickens, giving a greener appearance. Large park/golf and riverside greenbelt persist with little alteration.
notable_changes: Incremental housing infill on previously vacant lots, especially along the western and southern edges.
Conversion and densification of several central commercial/industrial parcels into mixed-use buildings.
Progressive increase in street-tree and backyard canopy coverage throughout residential zones.
Maintenance of the sizeable park and golf course core with minimal built encroachment.
Riverside corridor shows minor riparian restoration but no significant new construction.
